&lt;p&gt;I wonder if there is a way to preview all workspaces simultaneously and see what windows are opened on them. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;p.s. For example like in gnome shell when you touch left top corner.&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/6015/how-to-make-a-workspaces-preview/?answer=6016#post-id-6016</link><description>Not in (pure) i3 since this requires compositing and i3 is not a compositing window manager. 

However, as long as your X server has compositing enabled (which it most likely will), you can use an external tool such as skippy-xd. </description><pubDate>Sun, 24 May 2015 08:36:44 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/6015/how-to-make-a-workspaces-preview/?answer=6016#post-id-6016</guid></item></channel></rss>